{"lemma":"فِصاحٌ","slug":"فِصاحٌ","root":"ف.ص.ح","root_slug":"ف-ص-ح","root_link":"/words/roots/ف-ص-ح","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":1,"pos_tags":["adj"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":5},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n33971"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D9%81%D9%90%D8%B5%D8%A7%D8%AD%D9%8C"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"adj","gloss":"pure in language (especially of literary Arabic)"},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"eloquent"},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"fluent"},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"loquacious, voluble"},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"clear and distinct in speech"}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"فَعِيل (faʕīl)-type stative-verb derived from the active participle from the verb فَصُحَ (faṣuḥa, “to become eloquent”)."},"ipa":["/fa.sˤiːħ/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n33971","headword_ar":"فَصِيحٌ","root":"fSH","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"Milk"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"divested of the froth,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, A,) and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"clear of its biestings;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(A:) or milk"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"that has come after the ceasing of the biestings;"},{"kind":"text","text":"as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fiSoHN","text_ar":"فِصْحٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":". (Lh, TA.) ―         -b2-  [And hence,] (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Chaste,"},{"kind":"text","text":"as meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"free from barbarousness:"},{"kind":"text","text":"applied in this sense to a word, or an expression, and to language in general, and to a speaker, or writer: i. e.,] as applied to a word, or an expression, it means ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"free from an incongruous combination of letters and from strangeness and from contrariety to analogy not sanctioned by frequency of usage among the Arabs of pure speech;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faSaAHapN","text_ar":"فَصَاحَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", below:) or]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of which the beauty is perceived by hearing:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K:) and as applied to language in general, ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"free from weakness of construction and from incongruity of works, with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faSaAHap","text_ar":"فَصَاحَة"},{"kind":"text","text":"(which see again)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in the words themselves:"},{"kind":"text","text":"] as used by the vulgar, it means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in which the rules of desinential syntax are observed:"},{"kind":"text","text":"syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"muEorabN","text_ar":"مُعْرَبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (L;) [and sometimes it means]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"eloquent;"},{"kind":"text","text":"syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baliygN","text_ar":"بَلِيغٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". [from which it is properly distinct]: (S:) and as applied to a man, ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"possessing a faculty whereby he is enabled to express what he desires, with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faSaAHap","text_ar":"فَصَاحَة"},{"kind":"text","text":"(which see again)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in languages"},{"kind":"text","text":"or]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"clear, perspicuous,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"distinct, in speech,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"language;"},{"kind":"text","text":"as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faSoHN","text_ar":"فَصْحٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (K;) but this latter is an intensive epithet, [being originally an inf. n.,] like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EadolN","text_ar":"عَدْلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (TA:) [and sometimes it signifies]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"eloquent;"},{"kind":"text","text":"syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"balaygN","text_ar":"بَلَيغٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[respecting which see what precedes]: (S, A:) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"munoTaliqu All~isaAni","text_ar":"مُنْطَلِقُ اللِّسَانِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"free from impediment of the tongue,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"eloquent,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"chaste,"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in speech, who knows how to distinguish what is good in language from what is bad:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA;) the pl. as applied to men is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fuSaHaA='i","text_ar":"فُصَحَا=ءِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fiSaAHN","text_ar":"فِصَاحٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fuSuHN","text_ar":"فُصُحٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K, TA,) the last formed in the manner of the broken pl. of a subst., like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"quDubN","text_ar":"قُضُبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qaDiybN","text_ar":"قَضِيبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (Sb, TA:) the fem. is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faSiyHapN","text_ar":"فَصِيحَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; of which the pl. is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fiSaAHN","text_ar":"فِصَاحٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faSaAy^iHu","text_ar":"فَصَايِحُ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (K, TA.) And you say"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rajulN faSiyHu","text_ar":"رَجُلٌ فَصِيحُ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"All~isaAni","text_ar":"اللِّسَانِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A man whose tongue speaks Arabic correctly."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"lisaAnN faSiyHN","text_ar":"لِسَانٌ فَصِيحٌ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"i. q."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TaloqN","text_ar":"طَلْقٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A tongue free from impediment,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"eloquent,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"chaste in speech"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (S:) or (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"an eloquent tongue."},{"kind":"text","text":"(A.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faSiyHN","text_ar":"فَصِيحٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies also (assumed tropical:)  Any one"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"having the faculty of speech;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S;) [i. e.]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a human being;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aEojamu","text_ar":"اَعْجَمُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"meaning that which is “ destitute of the faculty of speech; ” (S;) [i. e.] “ a beast; ” as also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SaAmtN","text_ar":"صَامتٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": whence the saying,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"lahu maAlN faSiyHN","text_ar":"لَهُ مَالٌ فَصِيحٌ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"waSaAmitN","text_ar":"وَصَامِتٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)  [as though meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He has property consisting of human beings and of beasts:"},{"kind":"text","text":"but see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SaAmitN","text_ar":"صَامِتٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (TA.) And it also occurs in poetry as meaning (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Clear,"},{"kind":"text","text":"applied to the cry of an ass. (L.)"}],"source_refs":["S","A","K","TA","Sb"]}]},"classical_definitions":{"source":"hawramani","url":"https://arabiclexicon.hawramani.com/%D9%81%D8%B5%D8%A7%D8%AD/","headword_ar":"فصاحة","entries":[{"lexicon_id":"dictionary_18","lexicon_en":"Al-Sharīf al-Jurjānī, Kitāb al-Taʿrīfāt (d. 1413 CE)","lexicon_ar":"كتاب التعريفات للشريف الجرجاني","permalink":"https://arabiclexicon.hawramani.com/?p=23472#79c79c","body_html":"<span>الفصاحة: في اللغة عبارة عن الإبانة والظهور، وهي في المفرد: خلوصه من تنافر الحروف والغرابة ومخالفة القياس، وفي الكلام: خلوصه من ضعف التأليف وتنافر الكلمات مع فصاحتها، احترز به على نحو: زيد أجلل، وشعره مستشزر، وأنفه مسرج، وفي المتكلم: ملكة يقتدر بها على التعبير عن المقصود بلفظ فصيح.</span>"}]}}